Comment.Text: The processing pipeline is sligthly different from the p300-speller-4-online-with-monitoring. Here a mixture of experts is used for the spatial filters and the classifiers, instead of only one set of spatial filters and one classifier.
This is the part that buffers all the data and then computes the spatial filters and classifier after 10 symbols have been selected (the number 10 is hardcoded in the ovexP300Visualiser.cpp file)

This scenario is the subject independent scenario that can be used to skip calibration. One can immediately start in free spelling mode (on the same hardware on which the models have been trained, otherwise you should find another optimal delay). After a session of 10 letters, it will automatically compute a new spatial filter and classifier based on the predictions.
